                    "description": "Tax audits and appeal procedures:\nA part of the activities involve support to companies that are involved in tax audits or discussions with the tax authorities.  This includes preparing the (tax) file for the tax audit, assisting the company in meetings with the tax authorities, drafting letters and also representation during appeal procedures with the tax authorities and in court.  I have grown from the person actually performing these activities to introducing the Deloitte team members and managing the process.  In this respect, progress of the project, commitment of the persons involved and quality assurance are my main responsibilities.\n\nSupply chain management:\nMy projects included a supply chain restructuring whereby the production of the goods was shifted from various jurisdictions worldwide to one location in the Far East.  This included a complete new business set-up and model of doing business worldwide using one central entrepreneur.  Our team has assisted the indirect tax feasibility study as well coordination of defining all compliance obligations for 13 countries.  This included VAT, customs duty calculation, customs and VAT optimization procedures, high level legal requirements and the draft set-up of a process manual to incorporate this in the international organization. My role was a combination of controlling the quality of the content as well as supervising the project and the coordination with the client.",
